Completed the course of Introduction to Cybercrime

1. Overview
This document explains the basics of cybercrime and why it is important for anyone starting a career in cybersecurity. It helps in understanding how crimes are carried out using computers and the internet.

2. What is Cybercrime?
Cybercrime refers to illegal activities that are done using computers, mobile devices, or the internet. These crimes are usually carried out to steal data, money, or personal information, or to harm systems and users.

3. Why Cybercrime Happens

Cybercrime happens mainly because:
Attackers want to make money
Personal or sensitive data is valuable
Many users are not aware of online threats
Technology is widely used, but not always secured

4. Common Types of Cybercrime

Phishing: Tricking users into sharing sensitive information
Hacking: Gaining unauthorized access to systems
Identity Theft: Stealing personal details of users
Online Fraud: Scams related to money or fake offers

5. Impact of Cybercrime

Cybercrime can affect:
Individuals (loss of money or privacy)
Companies (data breaches and financial loss)
Governments (security and trust issues)

6. Why Cybercrime Matters in Cybersecurity

To protect systems and users, cybersecurity professionals must understand how cybercrimes happen. Knowing the methods used by attackers helps in preventing future attacks.

7. What I Learned from This Topic

This topic helped me understand that cybersecurity is not only about technology, but also about user awareness, behavior, and prevention.
